Critical rules:
- Do not rebuild Phase 01–08.
- Do not remove Phase 7.10 collaboration/federation behavior.
- Do not change backend port from 8005.
- Do not introduce localhost:8000 anywhere.
- Do not commit .env or secrets.
- Do not expose secrets in frontend.
- Do not log passwords, JWTs, API keys, refresh tokens, Cloudflare tokens, tunnel tokens, or provider tokens.
- Do not enable live trading by default.
- Do not enable real IoT actions by default.
- Do not enable real social posting by default.
- Do not bypass Guardian risk checks.
- Do not bypass content approval checks.
- Do not bypass tenant isolation.
- All external cloud integrations must be dry-run or template-first by default.
- Cloudflare operator automation belongs in cvsz/zeaz-platform, not cvsz/zdash.
- zDash may include safe templates/docs/scripts only.

